[1] Cholera - Liberia
Date: Wed 27 Oct 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and The News (Monrovia) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200410270045.html>

Cholera kills 4, hundreds affected in Maryland, Grand Kru counties
-----------------------------------------------
A severe outbreak of cholera has claimed the lives of at least 4 persons,
while about 435 others were reportedly affected by the epidemic in the
Southeastern Liberian counties of Maryland and Grand Kru. Merlin's Clinical
Supervisor in Maryland County, Ayeason Yeeba, confirmed news of the
outbreak in the 2 counties and said that 121 cholera cases were treated
between the period 11-30 Jun 2004 at the J.J. Dossen Hospital and other
health centers in Maryland County.
During this period, according to Mr. Yeeba, one death (a 13-year-old
female) was reported. 118 cholera patients were treated, and subsequently
discharged, in July 2004, while 60 cases were treated, with at least 2
deaths reported during this period. The victims were males under 5 years of
age. Mr. Yeeba also disclosed that 136 cases were treated in September 2004
alone, with the death of a 60-year-old female recorded, bringing the number
of deaths to 4 so far. [The number of cases treated in each time period is
unclear from this newswire, but the "gist" of this article is that there
have been 4 deaths and approximately 435 cases attributable to cholera
reported from Maryland and Grand Kru counties. More information from
knowledgeable sources to clarify this would be appreciated. - Mod.MPP]
[Byline: A. Wehdoe Sloh]
