[3] Cholera - Senegal
Date: Tue 2 Nov 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Yahoo Asia News [edited]
<http://asia.news.yahoo.com/041102/ap/d863qdt00.html>

Senegal Cholera epidemic spreads to 400
-----------------------------------------
A cholera epidemic in Dakar, the capital of this West African nation, was
spreading on Tuesday [2 Nov 2004], with 400 cases reported, and 2 deaths so
far, health officials said. The figure is up from 84 cases reported on 26
Oct 2004. The 1st case was diagnosed 11 Oct 2004.
While more cases are expected, doctors were optimistic about checking the
spread of the waterborne disease soon.
"This is the normal evolution of an epidemic...the preventive measures we
are currently taking will help us reduce the speed at which the disease is
spreading," Dr. Papa Salif Sow, head of infectious diseases at Dakar's Fann
teaching hospital, told The Associated Press.
The epidemic is still mainly present in the capital, Dakar. 2 cases have
been reported in Bambey, 123 km (76 miles) north of Dakar, Sow said.
The last cholera outbreak in Senegal, in 1996, killed 201 people.
[Byline: Nafi Diouf]
